    "description": "Inui Global Logistics Co., Ltd., together with its subsidiaries, provides shipping, warehousing, and realty services in Japan, New Zealand, Singapore, rest of Asia, Oceania, Europe, the Middle East, North America, South America, and internationally. It operates in three segments: Ocean Shipping Business; Warehousing and Transportation Business; and Real Estate Business. The company offers dry bulk services; ship operation and chartering; vessel operating and leasing; and transportation services for various products, such as grain, coal, lumber, nonferrous metals, and other dry bulk cargoes. It also provides warehousing services, such as storage/cargo handling, distributive processing, and delivery; logistics services comprising sea/air transportation, custom clearance, and inland distribution services; document and media storage services; and confidential documents disposal services. In addition, the company is involved in the leasing of residential properties. The company was formerly known as Inui Warehouse Co., Ltd. and changed its name to Inui Warehouse Co., Ltd. in October 2014. Inui Warehouse Co., Ltd. was founded in 1904 and is headquartered in Chuo, Japan."
